Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_proto_model(25.10)                                  get_proto_model(25.10)

Name
       get_proto_model  -  Retrieves all the information that you specify on a
       model in a design

Syntax
       get_proto_model

       [-help]

        [-committed]

        [-create_optimize_effort]

       [-exclude <string>]

       [-file]

       [-flip_table]

       [-include_default]

        [-tcl]

        {-all | -model  <<string>>  |  {[-type_match  {flex_module  flex_inst-
       group}] [-source_match {user auto}] }}

        [-name  |  -type   |  -create_total_area  | -create_gate_area  | -cre-
       ate_gate_count  | -create_area_per_gate  | -create_extra_macro | -plan-
       Design_target_util | -flexfiller_route_blockage ]

       Retrieves all the information that you specify on a model in a  design.
       You  can retrieve information on all the models or based on your search
       criteria and also on a specific module name. This commands returns  the
       following  information  about set_proto_model parameters in the Innovus
       console:

              * Parameter name

              * Current value

              * Type (Boolean, string, and so on)

              * Whether the current value was set by user

       If you do not specify a parameter, the Innovus software returns  values
       for all of the set_proto_model parameters.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each get_proto_model parameter. For  a  detailed
              description  of  the  command and all of its parameters, use the
              man command:  man get_proto_model

       -all   Reports the attributes of all modules.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -committed
              Reports attributes of committed models only.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -create_area_per_gate
              Reports the specified area per gate value.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -create_total_area
              Reports the total area including the standard cell area and  the
              macro area.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -create_extra_macro
              Reports the specified additional macros.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -create_gate_area
              Reports the specified gate area value.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -create_gate_count
              Reports the specified gate count value.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -create_optimize_effort
              Reports the specified optimization setting.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -exclude <string  >
              Excludes specified option.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -file  Allows you to output results to a file.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -flexfiller_route_blockage
              Reports percentages of flexFiller route blockage.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -flip_table
              Flips orientation of the table.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -include_default
              Includes  public  options with default parameters in parentheses
              (for non-tcl output).

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -model <string>
              Reports the attributes of specified models.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -name  Reports the module name.

              Note: Does not support wildcards.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -planDesign_target_util <number>
              Specifies the target utilization value to derive initial  module
              size of a model.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -source_match {user auto}
              Specifies  source  type for reporting. Valid values are user and
              auto.

              Data_type: enum_list, optional

       -tcl   Reports the model as Tcl list.

              Default: table print

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -type  Reports the module type.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -type_match {flex_module flex_instgroup}
              Specifies the type match for reporting.

              Default: flex_module

              Data_type: enum_list, optional

Examples
              * The following  get_proto_model  command  retrieves  the  type,
                source,  total area, and the target utilization of the alu and
                crossbar modules.

                set_proto_model -model  alu   -type  flex_module   -create_to-
                tal_area   1000  -planDesign_target_util 0.75

                set_proto_model  -model crossbar -type full -create_total_area
                3000

                get_proto_model -all

                Model     type         source      create_total_area     plan-
                Design_target_util

                alu             flex_module         user                  1000
                0.75

                crossbar  full           user             3000

              * The following command returns the values of all models in  the
                Tcl list format.

                get_proto_model -all  -tcl

                {{name  alu}   {type  flex_module}  {source user}  {create_to-
                tal_area 1000} {planDesign_target_util 0.75}}

                {{name crossbar}   {type  full}   {source  user}   {create_to-
                tal_area 3000}}

              * The  following  command only returns flex module's information
                in Tcl list format

                get_proto_model -type_match {flex_module}  -tcl

                {{name alu}  {type flex_module}   {source  user}   {create_to-
                tal_area 1000}  {planDesign_target_util 0.75}}

